                <h2>How to get a Visa-on-Arrival (VOA)?</h2>
                <p>All you need to do is to simply fill in an online application form (service fee required). Within 3-5 working days you’ll receive a visa approval letter, which means your visa will be ready at your appointed airport</p>
                <p>Copies of the approval letter will then be forwarded to Vietnam immigration checkpoints only at International Airports (Noi Bai/Tan Son Nhat/Da Nang). Upon your arrival, find the visa-on-arrival counter, where all documents are ready to quickly issue your entry visa.</p>
                <h2 id="vietnam">When to go ?</h2>
                <p>There are noticeable regional variations among the North, Centre and South of Vietnam.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: -8px;">In general, the North tends to have distinct seasons with cooler climate than the rest of the country during winter (November – February), while its summer (June – August) offers hot and humid weather with both sunshine and rain. Central Vietnam experiences warmer weather between July - October and wet, colder weather during November - April. Since its temperature remains constantly high of averagely 28-35 degrees Celsius all year round, the South simply has two seasons: wet (May – November) and dry (December – April). Avoid visiting this area from June to August, when it features the highest rainfall of the year if you don’t plan to get wet.</p>
