                        <h4>Nha Trang</h4>
                        <p>Added to its splendour, Nha Trang’s shorelines has recently been renovated, with lovely parks and sculpture gardens stretching along impressive pavements. Another way to spend your leisure time besides exploring its legendary clear blue seas and crystal white sands is to laze at a gorgeous classy beachfront resort.</p>
                        <p>Suggested places to visit: Doc Let beach. After unwinding yourself by the beach, you may wish to visit Nha Trang Cathedral, an elegant French Gothic styled building constructed in the 1930s, overlooking a train station. The Vinpearl Land, Vinpearl Golf, Po Nagar Tower or the Panduranga (Thap Cham – Phan Rang) in the central area and the Museum of National Oceanography further to the South Coast area are also worth considering.</p>
                        <p>Peak season: March – October.</p>
                        <p>Low season: November – February.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
