                        <h4>Hoi An</h4>
                        <p>Hoi An owns an exceptionally well-preserved Ancient Town on Vietnam’s central coast. The town’s history is reflected in its multicultural architecture from its Japanese Covered Bridge, wooden Chinese temples to the colourful French colonial buildings.</p>
                        <p>Highly recommended places to visit includes: Phuoc Kieu Bronze Casting Village, Tra Que Herb Village and Cam Thanh Ecological Village. The UNESCO world cultural heritage site My Son Sanctuary - the abandoned and partially ruined Indian Hinduism temples during Champa reign - is a little further.</p>
                        <p>Peak season: April – September.</p>
                        <p>Low season: November – March.</p>
                    </div>
