                        <h4>Da Nang</h4>
                        <p>Da Nang is a coastal city of central Vietnam known for its sandy beaches and history as a French colonial port. With the most modern newly built resort, hotel and restaurant system, Da Nang has recently emerged as a spectacular destination for world-wide travellers.</p>
                        <p>For those who’re interested in arts and galleries, we recommend Museum Of Cham Sculpture, where you’ll find the world’s largest collection of Cham artefacts founded in 1915. We suggest Phap Lam Pagoda or Cao Dai Temple as well, in case you’re more into religious sites.</p>
                        <p>Other attractions to visit: From Da Nang travellers can easily get access to Hoi An ancient town, Son Tra Peninsula’s Pristine Forest, the Ba Na hills and Hai Van pass, where you can contemplate the peaceful Da Nang Bay and the majestic Marble Mountains.</p>
                    </div>
