                        <h4>Phu Quoc</h4>
                        <p>An hour flight from Saigon, Phu Quoc lies by the Gulf of Thailand, best known for its stunning beaches, fresh air, cool wind and intact natural environment. It’s about time you savoured exquisite local seafood while indulging yourself in high-class services provided by the most luxurious hotels and resorts in this world-renowned quintessential island. Especially, do not miss the chance to go squid fishing!</p>
                        <p>Heavenly beaches to visit includes: Bai Truong, Ganh Dau, Bai Sao, Cua Can, Vung Bau, Bai Dai, Bai Thom, and Bai Vong. Besides white sands and clear blue water, each also has some distinct features for your consideration.</p>
                        <p>Peak season: During the period between November and March, Phu Quoc islands’ sub-equatorial climate with its consistent temperature of around 25-28 degrees Celsius plus lower humidity makes it the best time for tourists to come.</p>
                        <p>Low season: July – September can be wet and muddy due to the monsoon.</p>
                    </div>
