                        <h4>Hue</h4>
                        <p>Known as a UNESCO World Heritage site of history, culture and cuisines, Hue ancient city perfectly lies alongside the picturesque Huong River. The city biannually hosts the Festival of Hue, an art festival featuring local and international artists and performers. Hue’s also famous for its tranquility, where you are completely free from your bustling life.</p>
                        <p>Places to visit: It is advisable either to spend your precious time at the Imperial Citadel (Forbidden City), or to enjoy a dragon boat trip to Hue’s oldest pagoda Thien Mu before entering some of the Vietnam’s latest Emperors like Khai Dinh and Minh Mang’s Tombs. Additionally, Trang Tien Bridge, Dong Ba Market, Hue Royal Antiques Museum and the conical hat village are also recommended.</p>
                        <p>Peak season: October – March.</p>
                        <p>Low season: While the city is usually flooded in September – November, try to avoid July – August also if you’re not into the scorching heat.</p>
                    </div>
