                        <h4>Ha Noi</h4>
                        <p>Like no other Asian capitals as Bangkok filled with shopping malls, Singapore with high-rise towers or the modern metro-frenzy Tokyo, Hanoi remains a traditional developing capital with its renowned Old Quarter. Not only is it an economic centre, but it also includes many outstanding historic sites and other tourist attractions. Ha Noi Old Quarter specifically, is a unique character of this city.</p>
                        <p>Suggested places to visit includes: Duong Lam Ancient village, Ha Long Bay (Quang Binh), Sa Pa (Lao Cai), Tam Coc – Bich Dong (Ninh Binh). Furthermore, taking a bike tour to the majestic mountainous Mai Chau of northwestern Vietnam, which’s not yet a tourism hotspot, cycling through its rice fields and hiking to remote towns, or simply spending time enjoying your pleasant stay in Ha Noi with luxurious accommodation and excellent services, are all highly recommended.</p>
                        <p>Best time to visit Hanoi: November – mid February, when you can enjoy both the cold winds and the cosy atmosphere of western Christmas and traditional Tet.</p>
                        <p>Low season: March and May – mid June.</p>
